{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Embedding vector dimensionality matches vector index dimensionality.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"MOCK-MISS/MOCK-HIDE: a mocked embedder can always return the expected size and miss real provider/model dimension drift. REAL-INFRA: this boundary includes a real embedding API call plus real index metadata/config. LLM-DEP: not about nondeterministic generation quality, so no need to raise beyond System.","test_description":"Run the API against a real embedding model endpoint and real vector index (or its live metadata API). Send a fixed query, capture returned embedding length before insert/search, and assert it equals the configured index dimension; fail on mismatch or provider/model upgrade incompatibility.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.25,"System":0.6,"Agentic":0.08,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Similarity search returns results in descending cosine similarity order.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: stubbing ranking output can hide sort/metric wiring bugs. Minimum real failure boundary is query encoder + vector store adapter + scoring/order logic together. REAL-INFRA is not strictly required if you can run a real local vector engine/fixture; thus Integration is sufficient minimum.","test_description":"Seed a local test index with known vectors and expected cosine scores, execute similarity search through the actual repository/service stack (no mocked scorer), and assert returned scores are monotonic descending and IDs match expected order.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.07,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.25,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"LLM re-ranking changes order for nuanced-intent queries versus raw similarity ranking.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"LLM-DEP: correctness depends on real model judgment of nuanced intent, which mocks cannot represent. MOCK-HIDE: deterministic fake reranker would trivially pass while missing real failure modes. MULTI-STEP: only one agentic decision step (rerank), so Agentic not Workflow.","test_description":"For a curated nuanced query set, run real retrieval then real LLM reranking and compare top-K order before/after. Assert at least one query shows a meaningful order change attributable to intent (not random tie-break), with repeat runs to tolerate stochastic variance via acceptance bands.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.03,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"No-close-match queries return empty results, not low-relevance noise.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: thresholding and score interpretation bugs occur across retrieval modules and are easy to miss with mocked stores. A real local index + real threshold logic is enough to catch true boundary failures; external network is not strictly required for minimum.","test_description":"Populate index with a constrained corpus, issue out-of-domain queries through the full retrieval stack, and assert API returns empty when max similarity is below configured cutoff. Verify this using actual score outputs from the vector engine, not mocked relevance flags.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.04,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.25,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Median end-to-end query latency (embed + search + rerank + response) stays under 2 seconds.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA: latency depends on HTTP stack, network, serialization, and real upstream services/subsystems. MOCK-HIDE: in-process fakes remove dominant latency contributors and can falsely pass. LLM-DEP: pass/fail is timing, not model output quality, so System is sufficient.","test_description":"Execute a timed load test against the deployed API path with real embedding and reranking calls for a representative query mix; compute p50 end-to-end latency over enough samples (after warmup) and assert p50 < 2.0s.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.7,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.08}}]}
